comment._content:
I'm late to the game in this one and I'm sorry to begin with a correction of your title, that is in fact the North Circular Road at Doyles Corner with the New Cabra Road to the right of St. Peters and the NCR to the left!  The Garda/Policeman would have been based in the nearby Mountjoy Station and was a "D" District man.  
Doyles Corner was a notoriously difficult junction for traffic and a pointsman was generally posted there to manage the traffic and avoid accidents.  The late Dick Fallon who was shot on 3rd April 1970 would have performed traffic duties there for many years!
